Two children have died after being struck by lightning in the Nongoma area in northern KwaZulu Natal.Their father sustained serious burns from the same lighting strike.Storms in the area swept the roofs off several homes.The two children are the latest victims of the heavy rainstorms being experienced in different parts of the country&#8217;s interior.In Johannesburg, there&#8217;s still no sign of the body of a toddler who was swept away by the flash floods in Alexandra on Wednesday.Police divers on Saturday found the body of a six-month pregnant woman whose BMW was swept away on the N3 near Linksfield in the same storms on Wednesday.-SABC